# <type>: <subject> (max 50 characters)

# <body> (wrap at 72 characters)
# Explain *what* and *why* (not *how*)

# <footer>
# Reference issues, PRs, or breaking changes

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Commit Message Guidelines
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Types:
#   feat:     New feature
#   fix:      Bug fix
#   docs:     Documentation changes
#   style:    Code style changes (formatting, etc.)
#   refactor: Code refactoring (no functional changes)
#   perf:     Performance improvements
#   test:     Adding or updating tests
#   build:    Build system or dependencies
#   ci:       CI/CD changes
#   chore:    Other changes (tooling, etc.)
#   revert:   Revert a previous commit
#
# Subject Line:
#   - Use imperative mood ("Add feature" not "Added feature")
#   - Don't capitalize first letter
#   - No period at the end
#   - Max 50 characters
#
# Body:
#   - Separate from subject with blank line
#   - Wrap at 72 characters
#   - Explain what and why, not how
#   - Use bullet points for multiple points
#
# Footer:
#   - Reference issues: "Fixes #123" or "Closes #456"
#   - Breaking changes: "BREAKING CHANGE: description"
#   - Co-authors: "Co-authored-by: Name <email>"
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Examples:
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# feat: add user authentication
#
# Implement JWT-based authentication system with refresh tokens.
# This allows users to stay logged in across sessions.
#
# - Add login and logout endpoints
# - Implement token refresh logic
# - Add authentication middleware
#
# Fixes #123
#
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# fix: resolve memory leak in data processor
#
# The data processor was not properly releasing memory after processing
# large datasets, causing the application to crash after extended use.
#
# This fix ensures proper cleanup of buffers after each processing cycle.
#
# Closes #456
#
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# docs: update installation guide
#
# Add missing steps for Windows installation and clarify Node.js
# version requirements.
#
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# refactor: simplify database query logic
#
# Extract common query patterns into reusable utility functions.
# No functional changes, just improved code organization.
#
